<p>I'm trying to make an input autoresize to fit content (not bigger or smaller than needed)</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>form {   white-space:nowrap;   background: #ddd;   border: 1px solid #ccc;   margin:10px;   padding: 5px;   display:inline-block; }  input, button {   display:inline-block; }  input {   max-width: none;   min-width: 0;   width: auto;   -moz-appearance: none; }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;form&gt;   &lt;button&gt;-&lt;/button&gt;   &lt;input type="text" value="0"&gt; minutes   &lt;button&gt;+&lt;/button&gt; &lt;/form&gt;  &lt;form&gt;   &lt;button&gt;-&lt;/button&gt;   &lt;input type="text" value="500"&gt; minutes   &lt;button&gt;+&lt;/button&gt; &lt;/form&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>But width <code>auto</code> doesn't do the trick, at least in firefox,</p>  <p>Any idea why?</p>